The paper deals with information-theoretic aspects of coded caching, which falls under the umbrella of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the design of caching schemes for delivery over networks (cs.NI) and the use of memory-sharing techniques (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper involves optimization of caching schemes (cs.DS) and the use of machine learning techniques (cs.LG) to improve performance.
